        public Student addStudent​(java.lang.String SID,
                          java.lang.String unikey,
                          java.lang.String name,
                          java.lang.String preferredName)
                   throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                          java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Adds a new student to the enrolment system. This new student will not be enrolled in any units to begin with.

        Preconditions:
        None
        Postconditions:
        A new student with the matching data will be present in the system.
        Parameters:
        SID - Must match the SID requirements of Student. Must be unique in this EnrolmentSystem
        unikey - Must match the unikey requirements of Student. Must be unique in this EnrolmentSystem
        name - Must match the name requirements of Student
        preferredName - Must match the preferred name requirements of Student
        Returns:
        The student object that was created and added to the system.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if any of the uniqueness requirements are breached.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If any of the Student argument requirements are breached.
